<%= faq_schema([
  { question: "How do I add the signature to my email client?", answer: "Copy the generated HTML from the output box. In Gmail, go to Settings > See all settings > General > Signature, click the formatting toolbar, and paste. In Outlook, go to File > Options > Mail > Signatures, create a new signature, and paste the HTML. In Apple Mail, go to Preferences > Signatures and paste. Most email clients support HTML signatures natively." },
  { question: "Why use an HTML email signature?", answer: "HTML signatures provide consistent, professional formatting across email clients. They support clickable links for websites and social profiles, styled text with your brand colors, and proper alignment. Plain text signatures cannot include clickable links, bold text, or color, making them less effective for professional communication." },
  { question: "Which template should I choose?", answer: "Professional works for corporate and business environments with a clean, traditional layout. Minimal is ideal for freelancers and casual communication. Modern uses bold colors and rounded corners for creative industries. Colorful adds personality with a side border accent. Choose based on your industry and the impression you want to make." },
  { question: "Will the signature work on mobile devices?", answer: "Yes, the generated signatures use table-based HTML layout, which is the most compatible format across email clients and devices. Tables render consistently in Gmail, Outlook, Apple Mail, and mobile email apps. The signatures are designed to be responsive and readable on screens of all sizes." },
  { question: "Can I customize the colors?", answer: "Yes, use the primary color picker to set your brand color. This color is applied to your name, links, social media text, and accent borders. Choose a color that matches your brand identity. Darker colors generally work better for text readability, while brighter colors work well for accent elements." }
]) %>

<%= calculator_schema_with_ratings(
  name: "Email Signature Generator",
  description: "Generate professional HTML email signatures from name, title, company, and contact information.",
